{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/blog/petal-feedback","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1>Intro</h1>\n<p>Receiving suggestions, feature requests, complaints, and bug reports from users, like any other type of customer-focused evidence, is essential fuel for high-performing technology teams.</p>\n<p>NPS and satisfaction surveys, App Store Reviews, and customer support logs are all important sources of evidence for product decisions, but tend to be too generic, noisy, hard to categorize and measure, making it difficult for teams to focus on the right things and objectively measure the impact of product changes.</p>\n<p>How can we optimize the feedback channels so that we get measurable, contextual, precise, actionable information?</p>\n<!--\n\nThe first problem is overloading the customer support team with product feedback and feature requests. At Petal, we work very closely with our Operations team to understand the input they get by interacting with users, but we like to think that their time and expertise is much better spent helping people in need than categorizing desired features.\n\nThe second problem is getting feedback that is too generic to be actionable. Here, NPS surveys and App Store reviews are king.\nWhile important for other purposes, they both suffer from the same gap: feedback here tends to be framed as \"satisfaction with my experience in general\", and thus less likely to be immediately insightful. Additionally, when submitting this type of review, customers are taken _away_ from the experience of the product, and having to lean on their memory to describe their troubles and suggestions.\n\nLast, there's the problem of categorizing and quantifying. User-submitted messages that come via support, App Stores, or NPS are hard to group, parse, and measure. When reading feedback messages come in, it's easy to overreact to a sequence about a topic that is hot today, while ignoring another that has been coming consistently twice a day, for months. -->\n<h1>Requirements</h1>\n<p>Observing the challenges above, our requirements for our feedback tool were:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Measurable: We want to output a number that tells us if feature A causes more dissatisfaction than feature B.</li>\n<li>Specific and actionable: We want the ability to learn about specific moments in the user’s journey, specific pages in the app, and features we launch.</li>\n<li>Contextual: We want people to give feedback <em>in the moment</em> they’re interacting with something, not recalling it days or weeks after.</li>\n<li>Passive: We don’t want feedback prompts to interrupt the action someone is trying to perform.</li>\n</ol>\n<h1>The design</h1>\n<p>So here’s what we’ve built: a reusable feedback module that we can add to any page or flow in our app. By clicking it, users are able to provide immediate feedback about what they’re trying to do and how they think we could improve it. First, users are prompted to submit a 5-scale score, followed by a text field to explain why.</p>\n<div style=\"background: #8DE1FD\" class=\"w-100 pa4 tc mt5\">\n  <video class=\"w-100 mw5 br2\" autoplay loop muted>\n  <source src=\"/da7471cee6b822330d2f0f3a75f1a9f6/feedback-flow-3.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\">\n  </video>\n</div>\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 1800px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 79.11111111111111%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"feedback widgets 3\"\n        title=\"feedback widgets 3\"\n        src=\"/static/deb1f4103ca49cb9fbe9f516d30c1592/d61c2/feedback-widgets-3.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/deb1f4103ca49cb9fbe9f516d30c1592/fc2a6/feedback-widgets-3.png 450w,\n/static/deb1f4103ca49cb9fbe9f516d30c1592/1cfc2/feedback-widgets-3.png 900w,\n/static/deb1f4103ca49cb9fbe9f516d30c1592/d61c2/feedback-widgets-3.png 1800w,\n/static/deb1f4103ca49cb9fbe9f516d30c1592/b2313/feedback-widgets-3.png 2700w,\n/static/deb1f4103ca49cb9fbe9f516d30c1592/75ac7/feedback-widgets-3.png 3600w,\n/static/deb1f4103ca49cb9fbe9f516d30c1592/01600/feedback-widgets-3.png 4688w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span>\n<figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 1800px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 52.66666666666667%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"We produced two versions of the CTA. A larger widget to be placed in main pages, and a smaller one to be placed in modals\"\n        title=\"We produced two versions of the CTA. A larger widget to be placed in main pages, and a smaller one to be placed in modals\"\n        src=\"/static/b75671739f5e249e144fcdaac8ef4f4d/d61c2/feedback-widgets-4.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b75671739f5e249e144fcdaac8ef4f4d/fc2a6/feedback-widgets-4.png 450w,\n/static/b75671739f5e249e144fcdaac8ef4f4d/1cfc2/feedback-widgets-4.png 900w,\n/static/b75671739f5e249e144fcdaac8ef4f4d/d61c2/feedback-widgets-4.png 1800w,\n/static/b75671739f5e249e144fcdaac8ef4f4d/b2313/feedback-widgets-4.png 2700w,\n/static/b75671739f5e249e144fcdaac8ef4f4d/75ac7/feedback-widgets-4.png 3600w,\n/static/b75671739f5e249e144fcdaac8ef4f4d/3fbe3/feedback-widgets-4.png 3792w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">We produced two versions of the CTA. A larger widget to be placed in main pages, and a smaller one to be placed in modals</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n<h1>Results</h1>\n<p>First of all, we can now look objectively at how our pages and features are being evaluated by our users, and prioritize which ones need more work:</p>\n<figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 1800px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 53.11111111111111%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Easy to tell which page in the app the users are having the most trouble with. Data is randomized for confidenciality\"\n        title=\"Easy to tell which page in the app the users are having the most trouble with. Data is randomized for confidenciality\"\n        src=\"/static/00d4462e2fba220bc6e91f5ec4946564/d61c2/feedback-chart.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/00d4462e2fba220bc6e91f5ec4946564/fc2a6/feedback-chart.png 450w,\n/static/00d4462e2fba220bc6e91f5ec4946564/1cfc2/feedback-chart.png 900w,\n/static/00d4462e2fba220bc6e91f5ec4946564/d61c2/feedback-chart.png 1800w,\n/static/00d4462e2fba220bc6e91f5ec4946564/ae2f8/feedback-chart.png 2496w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Easy to tell which page in the app the users are having the most trouble with. Data is randomized for confidenciality</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n<p>Also, because the call to action is more contextual than an after-the-fact survey, individual messages become much, much more specific and actionable:</p>\n<figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 1800px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 36%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Refreshingly useful feedback\"\n        title=\"Refreshingly useful feedback\"\n        src=\"/static/112da3a634ca8cc6c9f9b651d73151de/d61c2/feedback-contextual-4.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/112da3a634ca8cc6c9f9b651d73151de/fc2a6/feedback-contextual-4.png 450w,\n/static/112da3a634ca8cc6c9f9b651d73151de/1cfc2/feedback-contextual-4.png 900w,\n/static/112da3a634ca8cc6c9f9b651d73151de/d61c2/feedback-contextual-4.png 1800w,\n/static/112da3a634ca8cc6c9f9b651d73151de/ae2f8/feedback-contextual-4.png 2496w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Refreshingly useful feedback</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n<p>By looking at and communicating the impact of design objectively, it becomes easier to earn a “seat at the table”, since these measurements can bubble up to company objectives.</p>\n<figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 1800px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 53.11111111111111%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Assessing the impact of design changes in user feedback scores\"\n        title=\"Assessing the impact of design changes in user feedback scores\"\n        src=\"/static/8db117487ed5ebfe76044e4a4fa94004/d61c2/feedback-chart-3.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/8db117487ed5ebfe76044e4a4fa94004/fc2a6/feedback-chart-3.png 450w,\n/static/8db117487ed5ebfe76044e4a4fa94004/1cfc2/feedback-chart-3.png 900w,\n/static/8db117487ed5ebfe76044e4a4fa94004/d61c2/feedback-chart-3.png 1800w,\n/static/8db117487ed5ebfe76044e4a4fa94004/ae2f8/feedback-chart-3.png 2496w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Assessing the impact of design changes in user feedback scores</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n<figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 1800px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 53.11111111111111%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Assessing the impact of design changes in user feedback scores\"\n        title=\"Assessing the impact of design changes in user feedback scores\"\n        src=\"/static/f26d50790b9ba3a4f1a498dca0ec8c81/d61c2/feedback-chart-2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/f26d50790b9ba3a4f1a498dca0ec8c81/fc2a6/feedback-chart-2.png 450w,\n/static/f26d50790b9ba3a4f1a498dca0ec8c81/1cfc2/feedback-chart-2.png 900w,\n/static/f26d50790b9ba3a4f1a498dca0ec8c81/d61c2/feedback-chart-2.png 1800w,\n/static/f26d50790b9ba3a4f1a498dca0ec8c81/ae2f8/feedback-chart-2.png 2496w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Assessing the impact of design changes in user feedback scores</figcaption>\n  </figure>","frontmatter":{"date":"February 15, 2020","path":"/blog/petal-feedback","title":"Collecting in-app feedback","topics":["Product Design","Research","Design Ops"],"subtitle":"Measuring user satisfaction in an actionable way","problem":"How can we collect feedback that is specific, measurable, and actionable?","solution":"Atomized feedback entry-points deployed across the app","impact":"Actionable, continuous app satisfaction measurements","color":"#8DE1FD","where":null,"learn_more":null,"learnings":["The shorter the distance between a user's pain and giving feedback, the more accurate and actionable it will be.","Your product is as good as your feedback loops.","The impact of design improvements is measurable and can lead to business and leadership action."],"team":["Dasmer Singh","Nicolas Moschopoulos"],"myrole":"Proposed, designed, and now manage the analysis of all incoming feedback","link":"http://www.petalcard.com","link_label":"Petalcard.com","cover_image":{"publicURL":"/static/15dd77281532daa7a4f030880ed90683/petal-feedback-2.png","childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/15dd77281532daa7a4f030880ed90683/73c85/petal-feedback-2.png","srcSet